# Changelog
All notable changes to **Phrasely** will be documented in this file.

The format follows [Keep a Changelog](https://keepachangelog.com/en/1.1.0/),
and this project adheres to [Semantic Versioning](https://semver.org/spec/v2.0.0.html).

---

## [Unreleased]
### Added
- Planned: PhraseDatasetLoader with ConceptNet + N-gram sources
- Planned: Evaluation module for clustering quality metrics
- Planned: GPU/CPU profiling support with `catch_time`

---

## [v0.1.0] – 2025-10-15
### Added
- Core modular pipeline (data → embeddings → reduction → clustering → medoids)
- GPU/CPU HDBSCAN support with fallback logic
- GPU/CPU TruncatedSVD reducer with auto-component clamping
- Unified logging and timing (`catch_time`)
- Unit tests for logger, SVD reducer, and timing
- CI workflow via GitHub Actions (pytest)
- PyCharm-friendly project structure and imports
- Initial `data/sample_phrases.csv` test dataset

### Notes
Stable baseline for future development.  
All tests pass, CI green, runs end-to-end on CPU or GPU.

